OL,4,Cinquiry into preventable deaths in
OL,5,Cnorth Wales
OL,7,FA PFD can be issued by a coroner if
OL,8,Fthey have concerns about the
OL,9,Fcircumstances in which someone died,
OL,10,Fand if it appears there is a risk of
OL,11,Fother deaths occurring. A PFD report
OL,12,Fbeing issued in a case does not
OL,13,Fnecessary mean the death itself was
OL,14,Fpreventable.
OL,16,FChief executive Carol Shillabeer has
OL,17,Fapologised to the families affected
OL,18,Fand admits they have been "let down",
OL,19,Fwhile the Welsh Government admits the
OL,20,Fhigh number is of "significant
OL,21,Fconcern".
